ol\": \"NewManagerImpl\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The major kubelet components owned by sig-node in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0 are: 1) Pod Lifecycle Manager: Implemented across two files - pod_workers.go (line 691 in kubelet.go, function newPodWorkers) handles pod lifecycle state transitions (SyncPod, TerminatingPod, TerminatedPod), and pod/pod_manager.go (line 663 in kubelet.go, function NewBasicPodManager) manages pod storage and mapping between static and mirror pods via the basicManager struct. 2) Container Runtime Interface (CRI) Client: Located in kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go with the kubeGenericRuntimeManager struct, created via NewKubeGenericRuntimeManager at line 714 in kubelet.go. This component interfaces with container runtimes through CRI APIs (k8s.io/cri-api/pkg/apis). 3) Volume Manager: Implemented in volumemanager/volume_manager.go with the volumeManager struct, created via NewVolumeManager at line 915 in kubelet.go. 4) Device Plugin Manager: Located in cm/devicemanager/manager.go with the ManagerImpl struct, created via NewManagerImpl at line 305 in cm/container_manager_linux.go. This component manages device plugins and device allocation to pods.\"\n}\nEOF\ncat /workspace/answer.json\n",
